					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That wouldn't help much I think. Even if I used another technique to find the exact edges of the walls, I doubt the NES would be able to do perspective-correct texture mapping on them as fast as my engine does now. The raycasting method is much simpler IMO, but we can only see what the rays hit. Unless we start shooting extra rays through walls or past the end of the FOV, but that could seriously affect the performance.<br /><br />What I'm looking for is a cheap trick, like almost everything else in this engine is. Walls scaled to 100% or less use 2 conseccutive 1/16 strips from the texture, walls scaled to 200% or more use the exact 1/16 strip that was hit, and I need to find a good enough rule for what's in between.</div>

